define_glitch_...ing_resistance(25.10)  define_glitch_...ing_resistance(25.10)

Name
       define_glitch_holding_resistance  -  Allows  you to specify the holding
       resistance

Syntax
       define_glitch_holding_resistance

        [-help]

        [-glitch_type {both | vl | vh | vlu | vho | vl_vh | vlu_vho}]

       [-instance_pin <string>]

        [-lib_pin <string>]

       -value <double>

       [-views <string>]

       Allows you to specify the holding resistance.

       You can use this command to define a  net-specific  holding  resistance
       instead of using the default holding resistance of 1000 ohms.

       This command can be specified more than once per net. If there is a du-
       plicate specification, then the last setting is used.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

       -glitch_type {both | vl | vh | vlu

              |  vho  | vl_vh | vlu_vho}" Specifies the glitch type for resis-
              tance Hold application. The option both applies the value to  VL
              and VH.

       -instance_pin <string>
              Specifies a list of instance pin names.

       -lib_pin <string>
              Specifies  the  instance/pin name of the driver that the holding
              resistance should be applied to.

       -value <double>
              Specifies the value in ohms of the holding resistance to be used
              by glitch analysis.

       -views <string>
              Specifies a list of view names.

              If this parameter is not specified,  then  by  default  all  the
              views are applied.

Examples
              * The following command sets the holding resistance on the Y pin
                of inst1 to 233ohms for VL:

                define_glitch_holding_resitance    -glitch_type    vl    -pins
                {inst1/Y} 233

              * The following command sets the holding resistance on the Y pin
                of inst2 to 380ohms for both VL & VH:

                define_glitch_holding_resitance   -glitch_type   both    -pins
                {inst1/Y} 233

